11:02 am  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  
Deft Lisa M. Kasten in court, in custody with Atty Stephen M Compton.  
ADA Diane M. Donohoo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Matter is before the Court for sentencing after revocation hearing.  
Court makes record as to charges and potential penalties.  
Court recognizes that there was an issue in terms of Atty Compton's concerns about DOC's activities in this matter.  He has documented that to the Court.  Court has reviewed Atty Compton's materials submitted in that regard as well as a letter of response from DOC.  Court makes record with regard to history of how this came before the Court today.  Court has reviewed Ms. Kasten's file including the sentencing transcript and those portions of the revocation materials that can be reviewed by the Court.  
11:06 am  Atty Compton has a letter from Ms. Kasten's daughter which he reads into the record.  
11:07 am  Atty Donohoo makes record as to victim's rights and restitution claim that is on file.  
11:08 am  Argument by Atty Donohoo.  
11:27 am  Argument by Atty Compton.  Court asks if feels he has enough information to proceed to sentencing today?  Atty Compton states he is absolutely prepared for sentencing.  
11:49 am  Ms. Kasten chooses not to make a statement.  The children have stepped out of the courtroom.  
11:50 am  Court makes record and proceeds with sentencing the defendant.  Court is not considering the recommendation made by the DOC in their letter.  

SENTENCE:  
Ct #1:  Total length of sentence is 3 years;  
1 year IC followed by 2 years ES;  

Ct #2:  Total length of sentence is 3 years;  
1 year IC followed by 2 years ES, concurrent with Ct #1;  

284 days of sentence credit;
ELIGIBLE for BOTH CIP & SAP;  

